<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Mobile Agency</title>

    <style> 
        html {
            scroll-behavior: smooth;
            /* This is the secret sauce for sticky menus */
            scroll-padding-top: 100px; 
        }
        body {
            background-color: #0f172a; 
            color: #f8fafc; 
            line-height: 1.6;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
            font-family: sans-serif;
        }
        nav {
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            background-color: #0f172a;
            padding: 15px 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #1e293b;
            z-index: 1000;
        }
        nav a {
            color: #38bdf8;
            text-decoration: none;
            margin-right: 20px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        section {
            /* This makes the page long enough so the links can actually 'jump' */
            min-height: 80vh; 
            padding: 40px 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #1e293b;
        }
        h1, h2 { color: #38bdf8; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <nav>
        <a href="#home">Home</a>
        <a href="#services">Services</a>
        <a href="#about">About Me</a>
    </nav>

    <header id="home">
        <h1>[Digital home]</h1>
        <p>Expert Web Development, Straight from Mobile.</p>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section id="services">
            <h2>What I Offer</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>A landing page</li>
                <li>A professional business website</li>
                <li>Anonymous website making</li>
                <li>School website making</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="about">
            <h2>Why Choose Me?</h2>
            <p>Why you should choose me? Don’t. Not unless you see my work for yourself...</p>
            <p>(Add more text here to make the section longer!)</p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2026 Tayief Sameer. Built on a Smartphone with love and care.</p>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
